The paper deals with the problem of establishing connectivity in dynamic networks, which is a core problem in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the study of distributed algorithms, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem of finding shortest, fastest, and foremost journeys in dynamic networks involves analyzing the topology of the network, which can be seen as a problem in network science (cs.SI). The paper also involves the study of graph classes and their computational power, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their performance, which can be seen as a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
